Powell, J., concurring; Voorhees, J., dissenting.
On March 6, 1911, the city council of the city of Newark, Ohio, duly passed a city ordinance fixing the maximum price of natural gas to be charged by The Newark Natural Gas & Fuel Company, its successors or assigns, for the period of five years next ensuing, at 20 cents for each thousand cubic feet of gas used or consumed by all person
